chain_of_thought_reasoning: To get the full names of superheroes with over 15 super powers, I need to join the superhero table with the hero_power table. I will group the results by the superhero's id and full name and then count the number of powers associated with each superhero. After that, I will filter the results to only include those superheroes who have more than 15 superpowers. Following the database admin instructions, I will ensure that only the full names are included in the SELECT clause, and I will rename the tables using aliases as T1 for superhero and T2 for hero_power.
SQL: SELECT T1.full_name FROM superhero T1 JOIN hero_power T2 ON T1.id = T2.hero_id GROUP BY T1.id, T1.full_name HAVING COUNT(T2.power_id) > 15
